sentence: Wall Street's main indexes opened higher on Tuesday as investors were hopeful of more stimulus from Washington, with Senate Republicans preparing to vote on a bill to help small businesses hammered by the COVID-19 pandemic.
ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average .DJI was up 0.65% at 28,378.18.
The S&P 500 .SPX was up 0.62% at 3,448.26 and the Nasdaq Composite .IXIC was up 0.41% at 11,525.657.
